frameDefinitions: An Entity has a particular scalar Attribute with a value exceeding a contextually-specified or generally-understood standard.
There is a gradable amount of light in a particular Location.

This frame concerns an Addict's physiological or psychological compulsive dependence on an Addictant, the substance or behavior to which the Addict is addicted. '' 'Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became hooked on that designer drug instantly.'
A System is perceived as complex depending on the intricacy of the interconnectivty of its parts or components.
A Rider is being transported in a Vehicle, or is moving on foot.
A Location is filled or covered with the Theme.
frameExamples: The small print was bearly readable by the light of the very <t>dim</t> torch.
Although she was never a big fan of drugs, she became <t>hooked</t> on that designer drug instantly.
San Diego freeways are a <t>complex</t> array of poorly maintained roads.
<t>Mounted</t> police officers are a common sight in this village.
The waters of the bay <t>teemed</t> with fish.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular gradable <fen>Attribute</fen> is appropriate and under consideration.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Value</fen> from the norm.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Value</fen> for the <fen>Attribute</fen>.
The place whose amout of light is being described.  The <fen>Location</fen> can also be a location in time, as seen in the second example below:
The entity from which the light eminates.
The <fen>Addict</fen> is physiologically or psychologically dependent on a substance or a behavior.
<fen>Addictant</fen> is the substance or behavior to which the <fen>Addict</fen> is dependent.
The complete entity or system whose complexity is under consideration.
The <fen>Rider</fen> is being transported by a <fen>Vehicle</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> covers or fills the <fen>Location</fen>.  This role most frequently occurs in a PP Complement headed by with or in.
<fen>Location</fen> is the object or area that the <fen>Theme</fen> fills or covers.  This frame element generally occurs as the External Argument.
The period of time during which the the Abounding_with event occurs.
listRoleExamples: She hid from the man in a dark <fex>corner</fex>.
A dim <fex>lamp</fex> swung over the entrance to the castle.
The waters of the bay teemed <fex>with fish</fex>.
<fex>The walls</fex> crawled with nanite surveillance probes.
